# riz

A shell function that adds color to [Ruby](https://www.ruby-lang.org/en/) documentation.

## Installation

* Clone
* Source into your shell: `source riz.rb`

## Requirements

* [Ruby](https://www.ruby-lang.org/en/).
* [ri: Ruby Information](https://ruby.github.io/rdoc/RI_md.html) is a
  command-line utility for accessing Ruby documentation. It should be available
  on any system with Ruby installed.
* [bat - A cat clone with wings](https://github.com/sharkdp/bat)

## Platform

Tested only on macOS (Tahoe 26.3).

Porting to Linux would probably require minimal effort.
